<F P=100> Lithuania </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russian Explosives Said Left at Nemirseta Base </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS3101150694 Vilnius RESPUBLIKA in Lithuanian 25 Jan 94 No 
16 p 6 </F>

<F P=103> WS3101150694 </F>
<F P=104>  Vilnius RESPUBLIKA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Lithuanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report under the "News From Europe's Center" </F>
rubric] 
  [Text] While withdrawing from the Nemirseta base [near the 
seaside resort of Palanga], a Russian Army unit left quite a 
number of dangerous explosives with unspecified detonators. 
Soldiers of the Lithuanian Army stationed there also failed to 
clear them away. Our servicemen are now moving out, and there is 
no shortage of amateurs in search of gunpowder. 

</TEXT>

