<F P=100> CAUCASUS </F>
<F P=101> Armenia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Karabakh Regains Lost Positions </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC3101194994 Yerevan ARMENPRES International Service in 
Armenian 1637 GMT 31 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC3101194994 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan ARMENPRES International Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Armenian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Yerevan, 31 Jan (ARMENPRES) -- Bloody battles 
continued yesterday in a number of war fronts in Karabakh. The 
Karabakh Defense Army completely stopped the enemy's offensives 
towards Mardakert, Martuni, and Gadrut. 
  On the same day, the Armenian fighters succeeded in taking 
under their control the previously lost positions near Omar pass 
in the north of Kelbadzharskiy Rayon. 
  Six fighters were killed and 18 were injured on the Karabakh 
side during battles yesterday. The enemy lost nearly 150 
soldiers and six armored cars, including four tanks. 
  The military operations resumed in the north of 
Kelbadzharskiy Rayon this morning. 
  The Azerbaijani Air Force planes bombed the settlements in 
Martuninskiy Rayon at noon today. According to preliminary 
reports, there are casualties. 

</TEXT>

