<F P=100> CAUCASUS </F>
<F P=101> Armenia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ter-Petrosyan Accepts Russian Plan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC3101162894 Yerevan ARMENPRES International Service in 
Armenian 1254 GMT 31 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC3101162894 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan ARMENPRES International Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Armenian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Yerevan, 31 Jan (ARMENPRES) -- The Armenian 
President Levon Ter-Petrosyan received Vladimir Kazimirov, the 
Russian president's ambassador on special missions, upon the 
latter's return from Stepanakert. They discussed Russia's 
revised initiative for the resolution of the Karabakh conflict, 
and the proposals it has submitted to the sides for a temporary 
and universal cease-fire and halt in military operations as of 1 
February, pending the implementation of the measures envisaged 
in the initiative. 
  Kazimirov held talks with Armenian Foreign Minister Vahan 
Papazyan and the Armenian president's ambassador for special 
missions, Davit Shahnazaryan. 
  The Armenian side has officially given a positive reply to 
the Russian proposal. 
  Earlier, Kazimirov met in Stepanakert with the 
Nagorno-Karabakh Republic leadership, who reiterated their 
desire for a political resolution of the problem and their 
readiness to enter into talks. 

</TEXT>

