<F P=100> CAUCASUS </F>
<F P=101> Armenia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Baburyan Urges Negotiated Settlement of Conflict </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0102122894 Yerevan SNARK in English 0926 GMT 1 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0102122894 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan SNARK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Stepanakert, February 1 (SNARK)--Karen Baburyan, 
acting as a chairman of the Karabakh Parliament, told Yerevan TV 
"The war should be finished and the problem could be solved only 
by negotiations". According to Baburyan, Nagorno-Karabakh and 
Armenia for many times showed their readiness to start the 
negotiations without any preliminary conditions, including the 
negotiations under the aegis of the intermediary missions. 
  Unfortunately, the official Baku took the opposite position. 
Saying "no" to the latest schedule of the necessary measures 
suggested by the Minsk group of the CSCE and the Russian peace- 
making initiatives, Azerbaijan follows the only way to solve the 
conflict -- by clashes. Baku also ignores all the attempts of 
the international community to achieve peace in the region -- 
Azerbaijan didn't send his delegation to the session of the 
European Council Parliamentary Assembly, Baburyan mentioned. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

