<F P=100> CAUCASUS </F>
<F P=101> Armenia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Internationalization of Karabakh Causes Concern </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD3101211494 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1854 GMT 31 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD3101211494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] At the request of the Nagorno-Karabakh authorities, 
the Armenian Foreign Ministry is now handling the issues related 
to the internationalization of the Karabakh conflict and is 
preparing corresponding messages to the UN Security Council 
chairman and the head of the CSCE Minsk group. This was stated 
in a document of the Armenian Foreign Ministry's department for 
public relations and press released in Yerevan on Monday. 
  The document says the reasons are the instances of Afghan 
mojahedeen involvement in the conflict on the side of 
Azerbaijan, the presence of a large quantity of Chinese-made 
arms in the Azerbaijani Army and British press reports, in 
particular, The Independent newspaper, about the possibility of 
British military aid to Azerbaijan. 
  At the same time, according to the Armenian Foreign 
Ministry, 
the above mentioned facts have not yet been officially 
confirmed. During diplomatic consultations the British, Afghan 
and Chinese sides denied information about any involvement in 
the Karabakh conflict. 

</TEXT>

