<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Combat To Be Halted Upon Withdrawal </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD3101193894 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1910 GMT 31 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD3101193894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [by ITAR-TASS correspondent] </F>
  [Text] Baku January 31 TASS -- Azerbaijan is ready to halt 
all combat actions in the zone of the Azeri-Armenian conflict 
provided the Armenian troops are immediately withdrawn from the 
occupied territories, President of Azerbiajan Geydar Aliyev said 
on Monday meeting Vladimir Kazimirov, special envoy of the 
Russian president mediating a truce deal in Nagorno-Karabakh 
conflict. 
  Aliyev stressed that the war is going on on the Azerbaijani 
territory. "Nagorno-Karabakh which is an integral part of 
Azerbaijan and seven other regions outside Karabakh are 
currently under complete control of the Armenian troops", he 
said. 
  The president resolutely rejected media reports on major 
losses allegedly suffered by the Azeri army and said it is 
Armenians who sustain most losses. "The Armenian units are on 
the offensive and therefore suffer bigger losses. We are waging 
a just war and defend our land from the occupants", Aliyev said. 
  The president used the opportunity to appeal to the Armenian 
leadership and the nation to halt the senseless war. "As the 
president of Azerbaijan, I guarantee safety to all Armenians who 
reside in Nagorno-Karabakh and their equal rights with all other 
citizens of Azerbaijan", he said. 
  The president noted that his country will never agree to be 
dictated by force and will never "sign an agreement humiliating 
for our people and state". 

</TEXT>

