Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Baku, January 31 (TURAN) -- The Adviser of 
Azerbaijani President for Foreign Policy, Vafa Gulizade told a 
TURAN's reporter that the government of the republic knows 
nothing about Russia's intention to bring its troops in 
Nagorno-Karabakh. 
  On Saturday [29 January] Russia's INTERFAX news agency 
reported that Russia prepares to bring its troops to the zone of 
Armenian-Azerbaijani conflict. 
  "We know nothing about that. I don't know the source of this 
statement of INTERFAX", stressed State Adviser for Foreign 
Matters, Vafa Gulizade. 

