<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   UK To Help Convert to CSCE Communication System </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2801210994 Baku TURAN in English 1738 GMT 28 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2801210994 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku TURAN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Baku, January 27 (TURAN)--The government of the UK 
has decided to give Azerbaijan special equipment, including 
computers and computer training read the official report from 
the British Embassy in Baku. 
  This equipment will enable Azerbaijan to switch over to the 
communication system within the CSCE framework. This 
communication system will provide direct, uninterrupted 24-hour 
communication among the capitals of the CSCE-member states. 
  The UK Embassy states that this communication system makes 
possible the exchange of information within the framework of the 
Vienna agreement on the Reduction of Conventional Weapons in 
Europe. The report also states that in contrast with offers to 
the other CIS states, no other state offered assistance to 
Azerbaijan in this matter. Taking this fact into consideration, 
the UK decided to give this equipment to Azerbaijan. 
  The British equipment will be delivered to Baku and begin 
functioning in the near future. 

</TEXT>

