<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Abkhazia Urges Yeltsin To Postpone Visit </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0102152394 Tbilisi Radio Tbilisi Network in Georgian 0900 
GMT 1 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0102152394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tbilisi Radio Tbilisi Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Georgian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Representatives of the Abkhaz government are urging 
Boris Yeltsin to postpone a visit to Georgia. On 29 January 
Yuriy Voronov, deputy chairman of the Abkhaz Council of 
Ministers, appealed to delegates of the second World Congress of 
Russian Unity to send a request to Boris Yeltsin to postpone his 
visit to Tbilisi. 
  In Voronov's opinion, the Russian president's visit to 
Georgia could result in bloodshed in Abkhazia because among the 
documents to be signed is an agreement on major deliveries of 
Russian military equipment to the Georgian army. Voronov said 
that Yeltsin's previous two visits to the region led to military 
conflicts, first in South Ossetia and then in Abkhazia. 
  Yuriy Voronov also called for the scrapping of special 
procedures on the Russian-Abkhazian border which are aggravating 
the crime situation in the border area. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

