<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Abkhaz Spokesman on Resumption of Hostilities </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0102151094 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1252 
GMT 1 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0102151094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Irina Shcheglova] </F>
  [Text] Sochi, 1 Feb -- The situation in Abkhazia's Galskiy 
rayon has recently been exacerbated, ITAR-TASS correspondent has 
learned from Beslan Bargandzhia, spokesman of the chairman of 
the Abkhazian Supreme Soviet. In his words, the Abkhazian side 
started preparations for deploying the peacekeeping forces along 
the confrontation line between the Abkhazian and Georgian troops 
on the Inguri river. At the same time several armed groups of 
Georgian troops crossed the Inguri river and penetrated deep 
into the enemy's territory. Exchanges of fire have resumed in 
Abkhazia's Galskiy rayon. People have been killed or wounded. 
According to Beslan Bargandzhia, the Abkhazian side lost 25 
people in exchanges of fire over the past month. 
  The spokesman believes that there is a danger that the 
hostilities in the republic will resume. He is convinced that 
it is necessary to speed up the deployment of the peacekeeping 
forces in the conflict zone, as envisaged by the Geneva accords. 

</TEXT>

