<H3> <TI>   `Alliance of Communists' Registered </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD3101191494 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1504 
GMT 31 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD3101191494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent] </F>
  [Text] Tbilisi, 31 Jan -- An Alliance of Communists of 
Georgia has been registered here, an ITAR-TASS correspondent was 
told today in the republic's Ministry of Justice. 
  In an interview to ZAKAVKAZSKIYE VOYENNYE VEDOMOSTI (this 
Russian-language daily newspaper of the Russian Defense Ministry 
is published in Tbilisi), Artem Azirov, a leader of the 
Alliance, said that communists favor the preservation of 
Georgia's territorial integrity and condemn separatism and 
nationalism. "We maintain that disruption of links with Russia 
and other fraternal republics is unnatural. It is unacceptable 
to oppose, as some politicians do, the closest and the most 
powerful neighbor, Azirov said. The course of the present 
Georgian leadership toward the rebirth of economic links within 
the CIS and the joint use of the potential built by the joint 
effort is worthy of all-round support." 

</TEXT>

