Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, January 27, RIA--President Boris Yeltsin has 
signed an instruction on appointing Gen. Dmitriy Volkogonov as 
chief of a presidential commission to investigate cases of 
missing foreigners and Russian citizens missing elsewhere. 
  The president has also signed an instruction on appointing 
Yekaterina Lakhova as chief of a presidential commission for 
female, family and demographic affairs, reports the presidential 
press service. 

