<F P=101> Russia National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Meets Karelian Supreme Soviet Chairman </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2701090994 Moscow RIA in English 0636 GMT 27 Jan 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD2701090994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow RIA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, January 26, RIA -- Russian President Boris 
Yeltsin today had a working meeting in the Kremlin with Viktor 
Stepanov, the chairman of the Supreme Soviet of Karelia, the 
presidential press service reported. 
  In the conversation held the Russian president was informed 
of the progress of reforms in Karelia in the bodies of state 
power and local self-government and of the adoption by the 
Supreme Soviet of a number of laws aimed at increasing the 
social and legal protection of citizens. 
  Much attention during the conversation was paid to the 
rational utilisation of Karelia's forest resources and also to 
the construction of Russia's first commercial railway line 
Ledmozero- Vacha-Kochkoma, which will make it possible to 
increase Russia's foreign trade in real terms. 

</TEXT>

