<F P=101> Russia National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russian Government Launches New Journal </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2101200794 Moscow RIA in English 1807 GMT 21 Jan 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD2101200794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow RIA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, January 21, RIA -- Issue No. 1 of 
ROSSIYSKAYA FEDERATSIYA (RUSSIAN FEDERATION), a journal of the 
government of Russia, is off the press. This is the only 
specialised periodical in the country designed for those 
associated with the governmental sphere, deputies and officials 
of bodies of state administration at every level. The journal 
will also be of interest to general readership, to anyone 
concerned with problems of the development of Russia's new 
statehood. 
  ROSSIYSKAYA FEDERATSIYA means information on how laws are 
made and how they work in practice, what deputies of the Federal 
Assembly are engaged in, and how the vital problems of the 
country and every citizen of Russia are tackled. 
  The journal will give detailed coverage to the course of 
constitutional reform and analyse the alignment of political 
forces in bodies of legislation and the positions of political 
parties and public movements. 
  Every issue will contain legal information, advice by 
experienced lawyers, answers to questions. 

</TEXT>

