<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   U.S. To Supply `Nearly $30 Million' for CW Destruction </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM0102125394 Moscow IZVESTIYA in Russian 1 Feb 94 First 
Edition p 2 </F>

<F P=103> PM0102125394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow IZVESTIYA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Aleksandr Shalnev: "United States Will Provide </F>
30 Million for Destruction of Russian Chemical Weapons"] 
  [Text] The United States will provide nearly $30 million 
to set up a research center in Russia which would devise the 
most effective methods of monitoring the destruction of chemical 
weapons. 
  Accord on this subject was finally reached during U.S. 
President Clinton's recent visit to Moscow and was formalized by 
a protocol which is confidential at the moment. According to 
informed sources, the center will be based at Moscow's 
Vernadskiy Institute of Geochemistry and Analytical Chemistry. 
Over one-half of the sum promised by the Americans will go on 
instruments and equipment. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

