<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Moscow Preparing Talks on Partnership for Peace </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0102120094 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1114 GMT 1 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0102120094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Russian Foreign Ministry is preparing for 
consultations with NATO leaders on Russia's possibly joining the 
Partnership for Peace program, Director of the Department for 
Cooperation with Europe Yuriy Ushakov told Interfax on Tuesday 
[1 February]. 
  He said that Russia intended to find out the NATO leaders' 
position in relation to Russia and determine the parameters of 
the agreements to be concluded. 
  The date of consultations has not been fixed yet. "However, 
they will take place in the near future," said the Russian 
diplomat. 

</TEXT>

