<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Opposes Air Strikes in Bosnia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0102151794 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1509 GMT 1 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0102151794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Ivan Ivanov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow February 1 TASS -- Russian Prime Minister 
Viktor Chernomyrdin said on Tuesday the crisis in Bosnia should 
be settled only by peaceful means. 
  "Russia stands against the escalation of the conflict and 
against air strikes" on positions of conflicting sides, he told 
a press conference. 
  However, the priemier also opposed the statements of Russian 
nationalist leader Vladimir Zhirnovskiy who said in Bosnia that 
U.S.-proposed air strikes on serbs would be viewed as an attack 
on Russia. 
  "This is an exaggeration", Chernomyrdin commented. 
  "The settlement of the Bosnian conflict is not an easy 
problem and it cannot be solved overnight", Chernomyrdin said. 

</TEXT>

