<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kozyrev Discusses Bosnia With Mediators </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0102142394 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1413 GMT 1 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0102142394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS diplomatic correspondent Georgiy Shmelyov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow February 1 TASS -- Bosnian peace process goes 
on is the opinion of Bosnian settlement mediators Lord Owen and 
Thorvald Stoltenberg, Russian Foreign Minister Andrey Kozyrev 
said here today after meeting the co-chairmen of the 
international London conference on former Yugoslavia. "The 
Russian initiative follows the same channel," he stressed. 
  The meeting discussed additional cooperation measures to 
prevent further escalation of regional violence, keep the Geneva 
negotiations process going and achieve Bosnian settlement. 
  The sides also focuses on a new Russian initiative that 
presupposes boosted efforts of the Security Council in order to 
develop the peace process, said Kozyrev. 
  Speaking of possible air raids in Bosnia, Kozyrev said in 
principle this measure is not excluded within the framework of 
Security Council resolutions but "it is an extreme step". The 
Russian foreign minister noted the need for additional 
consultations of the U.N. Security Council's permanent members 
and expressed the hope the raids will not happen. 
  The co-chairmen departed for Geneva after a brief working 
visit to Moscow. 

</TEXT>

