<F P=104>  Moscow Russian Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Vesti" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Intersept agency reports that members of the Russian 
State Duma have unanimously spoken against the president's 
forthcoming trip to Georgia. They believe that it is the wrong 
moment in time to pay attention to this unstable Transcaucasian 
state. Experts believe that signing a treaty between Russia and 
Georgia in the situation when problems of the North Caucasus 
have not been resolved may provoke a conflict between the 
executive and the lawmakers in Russia. Most deputies of the 
lower chamber will vote down the ratification of such a treaty. 

