<H3> <TI>   Grachev Leaves for Tbilisi </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0202094994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0910 GMT 2 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0202094994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Mikhail Shevtcov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow February 2 TASS -- General of the Army Pavel 
Grachev, Russian minister of defence, left Moscow for Tbilisi on 
wednesday morning to attend a meeting between the Russian 
president Boris Yeltsin and Georgian leader Eduard Shevardnadze. 
  Along with the signing of a treaty of friendship and 
cooperation between the two states, a package of agreements on 
cooperation between the military structures of Russia and 
Georgia is also expected to be discussed and signed. 
  Much attention at the talks is to be given to matters 
concerning the status of and conditions for the functioning of 
Russian border troops. 
  Expert opinion is that the prospective conclusion of Russo- 
Georgian military agreements does not mean the establishment of 
any military-political alliance between Russia and Georgia 
against Abkhazia. 
  The interests of both Abkhazia and South Ossetia are to be 
taken into account during the discussion of cooperation-related 
matters between the two states. 
  The problem of reaching mutual understanding over the 
question of carrying out peacekeeeping operations in Abkhazia 
with the use of a peacekeeping force under U.N. auspices will be 
one of important aspects of the forthcoming talks. 

</TEXT>

