1 </F>

<F P=103> PM0102210794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow TRUD </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [POSTFACTUM report: "Tbilisi Awaits Boris Yeltsin..."] </F>
  [Text] As a POSTFACTUM correspondent has been told in 
circles close to the Georgian Ministry of Security and Ministry 
of Internal Affairs, 20 of the Russian Federation president's 
security personnel have arrived in Tbilisi. The routes that 
Boris Yeltsin will take have been divided into five zones, and 
each of these into several sectors. 
  For their part, the Georgian special services are also 
adopting extraordinary security measures. In particular, 5,000 
policemen and around 300 Ministry of Security staffers intend to 
ensure security in the zone of the route that will be taken by 
the Russian Federation president 3 February. 
  As the Georgian Foreign Ministry has reported, B. Yeltsin 
will be accompanied by Russian Federation Foreign Minister A. 
Kozyrev, St. Petersburg Mayor A. Sobchak, and Defense Minister 
P. Grachev. 

