<H3> <TI>   Official Says Russia Will Deliver Oil, Gas </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0102121994 Kiev HOLOS UKRAYINY in Ukrainian 29 Jan 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> AU0102121994 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev HOLOS UKRAYINY </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Valentyna Pysanska report: "Energy Sources: Payment Is </F>
the Only Problem"] 
  [Text] According to Mykhaylo Kovalko, chairman of the State 
Committee for Oil and Gas, the situation that is presently 
taking shape with regard to oil and gas extraction in Ukraine, 
deliveries from Russia, as well as processing looks hopeful. At 
a recent news conference, he said that the branch had completed 
the past year successfully. The situation with the extraction 
of oil and gas had stabilized and the rates of construction had 
not decreased. 
  Agreements have been signed on the deliveries of natural gas 
from Russia in amounts similar to last year's; agreements on oil 
deliveries will be signed soon. 
  Do not ask me about prices or tariffs, because they 
constitute a commercial secret. I will only say that the 
agreement is mutually advantageous and will enable our national 
economy to function successfully. If only there are funds -- 
there will be energy sources! 
  This year, it is planned to purchase 32 million tonnes of 
oil 
from Russia. The Committee for Material Resources will be in 
charge of the deliveries -- partly through direct purchases and 
also in accordance with so-called Surgut [geographical name] 
agreements. A large part of the deliveries will be made through 
the group of companies "Nordex," which, last year, pumped 1.74 
million tonnes of oil, for which Ukraine has a debt of $123 
million. 
  The committee pins great hopes upon the implementation of 
the 
national program "Oil and Gas by the Year 2010," which specifies 
priorities in the development of the branch. 

</TEXT>

