<H3> <TI>   Radetskyy Decreases Number of Generals' Posts </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0102191494 Kiev UNIAN in Ukrainian 1401 GMT 1 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0102191494 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Kiev -- By order of Ukrainian Minister of Defense 
Vitaliy Radetskyy, generals' posts that were established in the 
Cabinet of Ministers and large enterprises of the military 
industrial complex in August 1991 have been reduced from 40 to 
29. During a speech summing up the results of courses of action 
taken for Ukraine's territorial defense, Ukrainian President 
Leonid Kravchuk approved the step taken by Vitaliy Radetskyy. 
Radetskyy also gave an order to remove all reserve officers 
from the military register who have not sworn allegiance to 
Ukraine. 

</TEXT>

