<H3> <TI>   State Budget Approved </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0102172294 Kiev UNIAR in Ukrainian 1630 GMT 1 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0102172294 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAR </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Kiev, 1 Feb -- The result of the afternoon session 
of the parliament session was the adoption of the state budget 
of Ukraine for 1994, with 255 deputies voting for its adoption 
and 36 against. According to the new budget, income and 
expenditure are equal, at 335.067343 trillion karbovantsi. 
  In the opinion of people's deputy Leopold Taburyanskyy, head 
of the People's Party of Ukraine, the new budget will lead to 
the further impoverishment of the population. In his opinion, 
expenditure on defense -- 16.82 trillion karbovantsi -- and on 
holding the March parliamentary elections -- 1.15 trillion -- is 
excessive. 

</TEXT>

