<H3> <TI>   Lukyanenko: Meshkov Goals `Not Obtainable Without Ukraine' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS0102114994 Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network in 
Ukrainian 0600 GMT 1 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS0102114994 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The process of Crimea's secession from Ukraine, 
initiated by the communist nomenklatura, has gone so far that 
the Crimea has in fact become an independent state. This 
opinion was voiced by Levko Lukyanenko, cochairman of the 
Ukraine Democratic Association, in an interview with the NOVYNY 
television and radio agency. Lukyanenko believes that Yuriy 
Meshkov's presidency is illegal, as were illegal Crimean Supreme 
Soviet resolutions to introduce the post and elect a Crimean 
president. Speaking of Yuriy Meshkov's possible activities in 
the new post, Lukyanenko pointed out that the Crimean Republican 
Party leader used to be a propagandist, while now he has became 
president and will have to take into account realities. 
According to Lukyanenko, Yuriy Meshkov's goal to improve the 
lives of Crimean residents is not obtainable without Ukraine. 

</TEXT>

