<H3> <TI>   Crimea's Meshkov To Meet Kravchuk in Kiev 4 Feb </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0102214794 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 2127 GMT 1 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0102214794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [by ITAR-TASS correspondent Pavel Kuznetsov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow February 2 TASS -- Newly-elected Crimean 
President Yuriy Meshkov and Ukrainian President Leonid Kravchuk 
had a telephone conversation on Tuesday to agree on a meeting to 
discuss a broad range of Kiev-Simferopol relations, Meshkov told 
ITAR-TASS over telephone on Tuesday. 
  The telephone conversation was described by Meshkov as 
"well-wishing and calm". The meeting will be held on February 4 
in the Ukrainian capital where Meshkov will go right after his 
inauguration in Simferopol. 
  In the words of Meshkov, "there are no reasons for any 
complications. The image of pro-Russian politician Ukrainian 
nationalists are trying to make has nothing to do with me. But 
this has provoked certain watchfulness of the Kiev authorities". 
  Meshkov noted the need for a stable Russian-Ukrainian union, 
referring to historical experience of both states. 
  "The time of Mazepa -- striving for isolation -- has gone, 
the epoch of Bogdan Khmelnitsky returns," the Crimean president 
told ITAR-TASS. 

</TEXT>

