<H3> <TI>   Hryb Promises No Change in Foreign Policy </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0102190894 Minsk Radio Minsk Network in Belarusian 1815 
GMT 1 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0102190894 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk Radio Minsk Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Belarusian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Myechyslaw Hryb, chairman of the Belarusian Supreme 
Soviet, gave a news conference today at which he made a 
statement expressing sincere gratitude to the citizens of the 
republic and to the leaders of the CIS countries who 
congratulated him on his election to the post of chairman of the 
Supreme Soviet. The statement also notes that the change of 
leader of the Belarusian parliament does not mean a change in 
political and economic course. No, good-neighborly relations 
with all states, all peoples, recognition of the borders within 
which we exist -- those are the main foreign policy priorities 
set out by the Supreme Soviet of the Republic of Belarus. 
  In the Supreme Soviet chairman's statement, he says he will 
support the course of nonnuclear status and neutrality 
proclaimed by parliament. Myecheslaw Hryb expressed hope that 
the Belarusian people will demonstrate a sense of organization 
and discipline for the speediest way out of the difficult 
situation in which Belarus finds itself. In the near future, he 
said, the Supreme Soviet Presidium, together with the 
government, intends to (?present) urgent measures to provide for 
the spring sowing and to take the necessary measures to activate 
the activity of our industrial enterprises. The Supreme Soviet 
chairman replied to numerous questions from the journalists. 

</TEXT>

