<F P=101> Belarus </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hryb Replaces Shushkevich as Constitutional Chairman </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0102173694 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1656 GMT 1 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0102173694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By BELINFORM-TASS] </F>
  [Text] Minsk February 1 TASS -- Myechyslaw Hryb, who was 
elected the leader of the country after Stanislav Shushkevich 
got a no-confidence vote from the Belarussian parliament, 
replaced the former speaker also in his position of chairman of 
the Constitutional Commission. 
  The republican parliament voted for that on Tuesday [1 
February]. 

</TEXT>

