<H3> <TI>   Democratic Forces To Resist `Kebich Dictatorship' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS0102192494 Minsk BELAPAN in Belarusian 1630 GMT 1 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS0102192494 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk BELAPAN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Belarusian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In Minsk, a regular meeting of the Conference of 
Patriotic-Democratic Forces has been held with the participation 
of the United Democratic Party of Belarus, the Belarusian Social 
Democratic Assembly, the Belarusian Peasant Party, the Christian 
Democratic Union, the National Democratic Party, the Party of 
People's Accord, the Society of Belarusian Language, and the 
Belarusian Association of Servicemen. 
  The participants unanimously described the dismissals of 
Stanislav Shushkevich and the "power" ministers as a 
nomenklatura's coup and a path to Kebich dictatorship, which 
will eventually lead to a collapse of the state and economy. 
  The members of the conference expressed their intention to 
unify activities of all patriotic-democratic forces to resist 
the dictatorship. Unification is to be discussed at the next 
meeting. 

</TEXT>

