<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Military Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Report Says Half of Armed Forces Combat Ready </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MK0102143094 Moscow MOSKOVSKIY KOMSOMOLETS in Russian 30 Jan 
94 p 1 </F>

<F P=103> MK0102143094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow MOSKOVSKIY KOMSOMOLETS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Russian Army Only Half Ready for </F>
Combat"] 
  [Text] MOSKOVSKIY KOMSOMOLETS has learned information from 
reliable sources about the state of the Russian Federation Armed 
Forces' combat readiness. 
  According to classified documents of the Russian Federation 
Defense Ministry, only 51 percent of Armed Forces personnel are 
capable of performing combat missions. Only one division in 
every military district is capable of taking part in combat 
operations, the Inspectorate for the Russian Federation Armed 
Forces' Combat Readiness reports. Only 20 percent of tanks in 
service can be considered combat ready. As for naval 
requirements -- putting a ship on full alert within 45 minutes 
-- only a few ships of the Russian Navy are able to fulfill them. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

