<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Military Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Discrepancies Seen in Armed Forces Strength </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MK0102144094 Moscow MOSKOVSKIY KOMSOMOLETS in Russian 1 Feb 
94 p 1 </F>

<F P=103> MK0102144094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow MOSKOVSKIY KOMSOMOLETS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "How Many Dead Souls Are There in Our </F>
Army?"] 
  [Text] It seems that even the Defense Ministry chiefs do 
not know the actual strength of the Russian Armed Forces. 
  In response to inquiries from the presidential staff, the 
government, and public organizations about the number of our 
servicemen, three of our highest-ranking generals gave different 
figures. Moreover, the gap between the figures amounts to over 
20 divisions. 
  Dmitriy Volkogonov said just before his removal from the 
post 
of presidential military adviser that 1.8 million men serve in 
the Russian Armed Forces. Colonel General Mikhail Kolesnikov, 
chief of General Staff, divulged that the Armed Forces include a 
total of 2.1 million servicemen. Defense Ministry Pavel 
Grachev, however, said that at present the Armed Forces are 
2.341 million men strong. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

