<H3> <TI>   Decree on Finance, Backup for Military Justice Organs </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM0202105794 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA in Russian 1 Feb 94 
First Edition p 4 </F>

<F P=103> PM0202105794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Decree No. 32 of the Russian Federation Government dated </F>
Moscow, 24 January 1994 and signed by Russian Federation 
Government Chairman V. Chernomyrdin: "On Resource Provision for 
Military Courts and Organs of Military Justice"] 
  [Text] For the purposes of ensuring the necessary 
operating conditions for military courts and organs of military 
justice, the Russian Federation Government decrees: 
  1. Until a legislative act in respect of military courts has 
been brought into force, the Russian Federation Ministry of 
Defense is to be entrusted with the funding, the supplying, and 
the material, technical, and other backup of military courts, 
the Military Collegium of the Russian Federation Supreme Court, 
and the Military Courts Administration of the Russian Federation 
Ministry of Justice. 
  2. The Russian Federation Ministry of Finance is to ensure 
the allocation of the necessary appropriations to the Russian 
Federation Ministry of Defense for the said purposes. 
  3. The Russian Federation Ministry of Justice, together with 
the Russian Federation Ministry of Defense and the Russian 
Federation Ministry of Finance, is to prepare within one month 
proposals for regularizing the pay of servicemen who are 
military court judges with due regard for Russian Federation 
legislation. 
  [Signed] V. Chernomyrdin, chairman of the Russian Federation 
Government 
  [Dated] 24 January 1994 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

