<H3> <TI>   Federation Chamber Discusses Draft Regulation Amendments </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0202104294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1025 GMT 2 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0202104294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Lyudmila Aleksandrova] </F>
  [Text] Moscow February 2 TASS -- The Federation Council 
(upper chamber of the Russian Parliament) started debating on 
Wednesday amendments to its draft regulations. The editing 
commission made 173 amendments to the draft. 
  Two amendments were made by the Russian president. He 
proposed that the upper chamber should take into account, when 
voting, the total number of Federation Council members (178 
under the constitution) and not the number of elected 
legislators (171) if the chamber votes on such decisions as 
release from the posts of upper chamber speaker and his depties 
as well as elections of members of upper chamber committees. 
  The presidential amendments were turned down. 
  The Federation Council continues discussing the draft 
regulations, and, to all appearances, the debate will take the 
rest of the day. 

</TEXT>

