<H3> <TI>   Chechens Seek To Free Khasbulatov </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM0202103594 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA in Russian 1 Feb 94 
First Edition p 2 </F>

<F P=103> PM0202103594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Gennadiy Gypylov report: "Chechnya Continues Efforts To </F>
Get Khasbulatov Released"] 
  [Text] Chita -- Chechnya continues its diplomatic moves to 
secure the release from the Lefortovo detention center of former 
Russian parliamentary speaker Ruslan Khasbulatov, who is 
regarded in the republic as having been unlawfully arrested. 
This was reported in an INTERFAX interview on Thursday by 
Eduard Khashkayev, a member of the Chechnya cabinet. 
  In Khashkayev's opinion, the October events in Moscow 
resulted from "a whole series of unlawful actions committed by 
the Russian leadership, which was opposed by Ruslan Khasbulatov, 
who strictly complied with all the provisions of the then 
Russian Federation Constitution." 
  Chechen State Counselor Ruslan Akhtakhanov, who took part in 
the conversation with the INTERFAX correspondent, stated that 
denying Ruslan Khasbulatov, who is a citizen of Chechnya, the 
opportunity to run for election to the Russian Federation 
Federal Assembly is regarded by the republic's population as 
another violation of human rights by Moscow officialdom. 

</TEXT>

