Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Tigran Liloyan] </F>
  [Text] Yerevan February 1 TASS -- Press secretary of the 
Armenian President Aram Abramyan has sent in his resignation. 
The resignation was accepted by the president on Monday night. 
  In the words of Abramyan, the reasons for his resignation 
are 
not political. He confirmed his loyalty to President Levon 
Ter-Petrosyan and noted he will return to scientific activities 
at the Institute of Arts of the Armenian Academy of Sciences. 

