<H3> <TI>   Parliament Approves Prosecution of Party Candidate </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0102214794 Yerevan SNARK in English 1533 GMT 1 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0102214794 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan SNARK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Yerevan, February 1 (SNARK)--Today the Armenian 
Parliament has almost unanimously given its consent to institute 
criminal proceedings against Myasnik Hakopyan, the chairman of 
the Council of Businessmen, Leaseholders and Cooperators. He is 
prosecuted for misappropriation of state property of great 
dimensions. 
  Artavazd Gevorkyan, the general prosecutor of Armenia, 
states 
the chairman of the Businessmen's Council misappropriated by 
means of machinations and forgery more than 34 million rubles. 
2000 cartridges were found during his apartment's search. 
  Myasnik Hakopyan was one of the candidates on the 
president's 
post. 
  The parliament's consent was necessary because 
Dashnaktsutyun 
Party had proposed Hakopyan as a candidate to the Supreme Soviet 
of Armenia. Therefore, Dashnaktsutyun demanded his immediate 
release and remonstrated at the Office of Public Prosecutor. 

</TEXT>

