<H3> <TI>   Border Shelling, Fighting in Karabakh Reported </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0102193594 Yerevan Armenia's Radio First Program Network 
in Armenian 1800 GMT 1 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0102193594 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan Armenia's Radio First Program Network 
in Armenian 1800 GMT 1 Feb 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Armenian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Azerbaijani Army units in Tauzskiy Rayon resumed 
shelling of border positions in Tavushskiy Rayon yesterday 
evening. 
  The Armenian Defense Ministry Press Service reported that 
tank, howitzer, and grenade fire was directed at Artzvaberd, 
Aygepar, and Chinari. The shelling lasted for 15 minutes. 
There were no casualties. 
  No serious incidents have taken place in the other border 
regions of Armenia since last night. 
  The Nagorno-Karabakh Republic Defense Army headquarters 
reported that no substantial changes took place on the war 
fronts last night and this morning. The Karabakh Army units 
successfully repulsed all attacks by the enemy in the northern 
region of Kelbadzharskiy Rayon. The Azerbaijani troops suffered 
substantial losses in men and material. 
  The Azerbaijani Army launched yet another offensive at the 
southeastern sector of the front this morning. 
  Only positional battles are taking place in the other 
sectors 
of the war front. 

</TEXT>

