<F P=101> Armenia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Accord Reached With Nakhichevan on Border Security </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0102195294 Yerevan ARMENPRES International Service in 
Armenian 1446 GMT 1 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0102195294 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan ARMENPRES International Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Armenian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Yerevan, 1 Feb (ARMENPRES)--A meeting of the 
plenipotentiary representatives of the Armenian Republic and 
Nakhichevan Autonomous Republic took place in Araratskiy Rayon. 
It was the continuation of the talks that started on 14 
January. The aim of these talks is to stabilize the situation 
on the borders. 
  A joint statement was issued in which the sides agreed to 
tighten control over the armed formations all along the border 
and henceforth not allow any hostile action against each other, 
such as the shelling of each other's positions and the violation 
of borders. 
  Chief Border Commissar Gegam Harutyunyan, who was heading 
the 
Armenian delegation, told an ARMENPRES correspondent that the 
dialogue with Nakhichevan is taking place in an atmosphere of 
mutual understanding and that this inspires hope that there will 
be an end to incidents on the Armenian-Nakhichevan border. 

</TEXT>

