<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   South Ossetia Appeals to Yeltsin for Security Guarantees </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0202110994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1041 GMT 2 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0202110994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Valeriy Shanayev] </F>
  [Text] Vladikavkaz February 2 TASS -- The South Ossetian 
parliament adopted today an appeal to the Russian president, 
asking him to "work out security guarantees of the Republic of 
South Ossetia, of its free and democratic development before 
signing the Russian-Georgian treaty." 
  Members of parliament adopted as well an appeal to the 
Federation Council and the State Duma of the Russian Federation, 
asking them to "refrain from the ratification of a full-scale 
treaty between Russia and Georgia until a complete settlement of 
Ossetian-Georgian relations and not to regard the republic of 
South Ossetia as part of the Republic of Georgia." 
  In its turn, the Information and Press Committee of South 
Ossetia circulated today a statement of the republican 
parliament, which pointed out that the signing of the 
Russian-Georgian treaty "while the problem of the status of 
South Ossetia has not yet been resolved, is direct violation of 
the previous four-party agreements. This infringement on the 
rights of the Ossetian people will inevitably lead to the 
escalation of violence in the Republic of South Ossetia and 
around it." 

</TEXT>

