<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russian Offer for Joint Defense Rejected </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0102210194 Baku Azerbaycan Radio Televiziyasi Television 
Network in Azeri 1600 GMT 1 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0102210194 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku Azerbaycan Radio Televiziyasi Television 
Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Azeri </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report on interview with Major General Mustafa Nesirov, </F>
chief adviser on border affairs at the National Security 
Ministry, by Sakit Ochaghly; place and date not given] 
  [Text] Talks and consultations are being held and concrete 
proposals are being put forward at the highest levels on the 
defense and inviolability of our borders. 
  [Begin recording] [Nesirov] Each state must defend its own 
borders, and borders should be defended by the border guards of 
a given state. We must defend our borders with our own border 
guards. We will undoubtedly achieve this. 
  [Ochaghly] Talks are being held on this subject. Are you 
taking part in these talks? 
  [Nesirov] The commander of the Russian border guards wanted 
us to defend the borders jointly. That is, Azerbaijan's border 
with Iran. We said at that time, and even earlier, and during 
the talks with Lieutenant-General (Mikhalayov) in Baku that we 
ourselves will defend our own borders. It will not be correct 
if we allow the Russian border guards to defend Azerbaijan's 
border with Iran jointly with us. It will mean the loss of 
sovereignty. We have a sovereign state and border guards. We 
must defend our own borders with our own border guards. 
Undoubtedly we will achieve this. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

