<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Five Killed in Explosion at Baku Train Station </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0202110794 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1039 GMT 2 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0202110794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondents Savinj Abdullayeva and Viktor </F>
Shulman] 
  [Text] Baku February 2 TASS -- Five people died in a 
midnight explosion which rocked the Baku railway terminal on 
Tuesday. Seven other people were injured and hospitalized in 
critical condition, after the explosion shattered tens of 
railway wagons. 
  The cause of the explosion was not immediately known. The 
train, in which one of the cars exploded when passengers were 
getting into it, arrived earlier from Kislovodsk, southern 
Russia. It was duly inspected in the local depot and put into 
service again because of the rolling stock shortage. 
  Competent sources close to the investigation of the accident 
do not rule out an act of subversion as the cause of the blast. 

</TEXT>

