<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Gaydar Says Draft Amnesty Law Disputable </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD3101142794 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1342 
GMT 31 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD3101142794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, 31 Jan ITAR-TASS -- The draft law on an 
amnesty submitted by the president to the State Duma seems 
extremely disputable. This is the view expressed by Yegor 
Gaydar, leader of the Russia's Choice parliamentary faction, in 
a conversation with correspondents today. Next Friday the State 
Duma will resume its sittings and the amnesty issue looks likely 
to be one of the items on the agenda. 
  "We are very doubtful about the provisions of the draft 
which 
reduce punishments for serious criminal offenses," Gaydar said. 

</TEXT>

