<F P=100> BALTIC STATES </F>
<F P=101> Estonia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Negotiators Meet With Russians for Talks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS0102193694 Tallinn BNS in English 1632 GMT 1 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS0102193694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, Feb 01, BNS--The Estonian and the Russian 
negotiators met today for another round of talks near Moscow. 
  On the agenda are the withdrawal of the Russian troops from 
Estonia, the social protection of Russian military pensioners 
living in Estonia, and other questions of bilateral relations. 
  Vasily Svirin, Russia's top negotiator, said earlier Russia 
will now present the detailed timetable for the troop withdrawal 
from January through August. 
  Svirin said the timetable contains the dates for the pullout 
of all units as well as the number of men serving in them. "We 
hope this gesture of good will inspire also Estonia to 
constructive action," the Russian diplomat said. 
  As reported earlier, Estonia accepted Russia's proposal to 
withdraw its troops from Estonia by Aug. 31, but insisted that 
Russia present a detailed schedule for the pullout. 

</TEXT>

