<F P=100> INTERREGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   CIS Assembly To Debate Chairman Position </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0202155994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1454 GMT 2 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0202155994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By Belinform correspondent Larisa Klychnikova for TASS] </F>
  [Text] Minsk February 2 TASS -- A meeting of the 
parliamentary assembly of the CIS will be held in the Tavria 
Palace in St. Petersburg on February 8-9. The delegations will 
be represented by heads of parliament of CIS countries. The 
assembly will concentrate on debating the candidature of 
chairman of the interparliamentary assembly, Ivan Korotchenya, 
executive secretary of the CIS, told BELINFORM. Korotchenya 
does not rule out the possibility of Ivan Rybkin or of Vladimir 
Shumeyko, Russian representatives, being appointed chairman of 
the parliamentary assembly. 
  The 15 items planned to be debated include legal regulation 
of relations between the CIS countries in the framework of the 
economic union -- coordination and unification of the economic 
policy and bringing closer legislations of states of the 
commonwealth. 
  The meeting will also discuss a long-range plan and results 
of the interparliamentary group's activity on peace settlement 
in Nagorno-Karabakh. 

</TEXT>

