<F P=100> INTERREGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Black Sea Fleet Spokesman on Ukraine Naval Chief's Remarks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0102133094 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1114 GMT 1 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0102133094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A spokesman for the Black Sea Navy Command has 
called on Ukrainian naval officials to refrain from "dangerous 
assessments running counter to the opinion of the Russian and 
Ukrainian presidents and to the spirit of the Russian-Ukrainian 
naval accords. [no closing quotation marks as received] 
  This statement came in reply to a cable addressed to the 
Naval Headquarters Chief, Vice-Admiral Svyatashov, by his 
Ukrainian counterpart, Rear-Admiral Ryzhenko, who has described 
the Black Sea Marine Brigade as "a foreign unit on Ukraine's 
territory." 
  The spokesman emphasized that in line with the Yalta 
agreement, the brigade, like the entire fleet, is subordinate to 
the Ukrainian president. Thus, Ryzhenko's declaration 
contradicts the document signed by the president as the Supreme 
Commander of the Ukrainian Armed Forces. 

</TEXT>

