<H3> <TI>   Envoy Confers With Polish Foreign Minister </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0202152794 Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service in Ukrainian 
2000 GMT 1 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0202152794 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Polish Foreign Minister Andrzej Olechowski has 
received Gennadiy Udovenko, ambassador extraordinary and 
plenipotentiary of Ukraine. Prospects for the development of 
bilateral Ukrainian-Polish relations were discussed during the 
conversation. The Polish minister stressed the necessity of 
strengthening good-neighborly relations with our state in all 
areas of cooperation, and noted that fast changes in its 
economic life and Poland's active help in this will facilitate 
the strengthening of Ukraine's statehood and independence. 
  In his turn Gennadiy Udovenko stressed the importance of 
continuing Poland's course toward closer cooperation with 
Ukraine, and informed his interlocutor in detail about the 
contents of the tripartite Ukrainian-American-Russian statement 
regarding nuclear disarmament. 

</TEXT>

