<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Plyushch Against Referendum </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0202170294 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1452 GMT 2 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0202170294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The speaker of the Ukrainian parliament, Ivan 
Plyushch, has expressed disfavor for a referendum on the basic 
constitutional provisions in Ukraine. The proposal on holding 
the referendum March 27 was earlier advanced by Ukrainian 
President Leonid Kravchuk. 
  Speaking in parliament on Wednesday morning, Plyushch said 
that the constitutional law on power should be adopted by 
parliament. 
  According to the draft law that is to be debated in 
parliament Thursday, the local executive power should be in the 
hands of the heads of locals councils who are to be elected. 
  The institute of the president's representatives, Plyushch 
proposed, is to be annulled after the constitutional law comes 
into force. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

