<H3> <TI>   Hryb Instructs KGB To Probe Strike Call </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0202162594 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1524 GMT 2 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0202162594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By BELINFORM for TASS] </F>
  [Text] Minsk February 2 TASS -- Belarusian Parliament 
Chairman Myecheslaw Hryb instructed the Republican KGB to probe 
the decision of the National Strike Committee which, according 
to him, contains appeals to topple authorities. 
  The Strike Committee decided on Wednesday to call an 
indefinite political strike on February 15. The major demand is 
the resignation of the government and early parliamentary 
elections. 
  "If there are criminal aspects in the issue, criminal 
proceedings should be instituted jointly with the prosecutor's 
office and an investigation carried out", Hryb instructed Acting 
KGB Chairman Gennadiy Lavitskiy. 
  Hryb informed parliamentarians about his order during the 
evening session on Wednesday. 

</TEXT>

