<H3> <TI>   Strikers To Form Worker Detachments, Adopt Appeal </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS0202213294 Minsk Radio Minsk Network in Belarusian 2050 
GMT 2 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS0202213294 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk Radio Minsk Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Belarusian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] [passage omitted] The Strike Committee at its 
meeting on 2 February resolved to form worker detachments for 
maintaining order during the strikes. It was also resolved to 
request the Belarusian Association of Servicemen to help 
maintain order. According to BELAPAN, Strike Committee 
representatives intend to request that the Armed Forces and 
internal troops not interfere in the upcoming events. A meeting 
with representatives of a number of political parties and trade 
unions is also scheduled for 7 February, during which the 
members of the Council of the Strike Commitees will detail their 
protest action. Due to organizational reasons, BELAPAN has not 
been informed of the list of enterprises that agreed to 
participate in the political strike. However, one can assuredly 
say that they include the largest enterprises of the country. 

</TEXT>

