Language: <F P=105> Belarusian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Half an hour ago, the 13th Supreme Soviet began its 
work. Deputies began the day with a discussion of miscellaneous 
issues. However, at the beginning, Supreme Soviet Chairman 
Myechyslaw Hryb declared that he received a proposal from more 
than 20 people's deputies to listen to a speech by the 
Belarusian Strike Committee chairman. This issue was voted on 
and was not supported by a majority of deputies. The deputies 
began discussing miscellaneous issues. 

