<F P=101> Belarus </F>
<H3> <TI>   Supreme Soviet Adopts Law on Vouchers </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS0202135394 Minsk Radio Minsk Network in Belarusian 1300 
GMT 2 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS0202135394 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk Radio Minsk Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Belarusian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] At the beginning of today's Supreme Soviet session, 
Chairman Myechyslaw Hryb congratulated People's Deputy Leonid 
Dzeyka on the occasion of his birthday. Next, the lawmakers 
began discussing miscellaneous issues. People's Deputies 
Shushkevich, Henadz Karpenko, Syarhey Antonchik, and others 
delivered speeches. Then, the chairman proposed to discuss 
several key issues. The deputies adopted the Supreme Soviet 
decree: "On Implementation of the Law of the Republic of 
Belarus on Joint Stock Companies, Companies With Limited and 
Additional Liability." The deputies introduced several changes 
and supplements to current legislation and adopted the Law on 
Vouchers. In addition, the deputies had the second reading of 
the law on state tax inspection in the Republic of Belarus. Two 
hundred and six deputies voted for the adoption of this law. A 
corresponding Supreme Soviet decree was also adopted. Later, the 
deputies began to dispute the law on pensions. They introduced 
some changes and amendments to this law. 
  The deputies are currently on a break. The evening session 
will begin at 1600 [1400 GMT]. 

</TEXT>

