<F P=101> Belarus </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russian Experts Arrive To Finalize Monetary Merger </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS0202135894 Minsk BELAPAN in Belarusian 1240 GMT 2 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS0202135894 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk BELAPAN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Belarusian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] According to reliable sources, a large group of 
Russian financial and economic experts arrived in Minsk today. 
The group also includes representatives of the State 
Cooperation Committee, Customs Control Committee, and the 
Central Bank of Russia. The visit is connected with 
preparations for the signing of documents necessary to merge the 
two countries' monetary systems. An official from the 
Belarusian Cabinet of Ministers, who agreed to speak on 
condition of anonymity, did not rule out a decision to gradually 
replace the Belarusian currency with Russian rubles sometime 
this year. Russian Deputy Prime Minister Oleg Soskovets is 
expected to arrive in Minsk later this week to finally resolve 
this issue. 

</TEXT>

