<F P=100> Moldova </F>
<H3> <TI>   Results of Visit to Strasbourg Reported </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0202143694 Chisinau BASAPRESS in English 1855 GMT 1 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0202143694 </F>
<F P=104>  Chisinau BASAPRESS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Chisinau, BASAPRESS, 1/2/1994 -- Alexandru Buruiana, 
chairman of Parliament Commission for Foreign Relations, back 
from an official visit to Strasbourg, told BASA that Council of 
Europe representatives he had met support the idea of a national 
poll in Moldova on its independence. "Experts of European 
structures believe that, though without juridical effect, such 
poll would not allow Tiraspol leaders invoke the reason of 
`eventual unification,'" Buruiana asserted. The Moldovan 
delegation met with Catherine Lalumiere, Secretary General of 
Council of Europe and discussed the Ilascu group problem, 
working out future steps for releasing the political prisoners. 
At meetings with top European dignitaries between January 19th 
and 29th, questions regarding Moldova's adherence to the Council 
of Europe were examined. Recommendations were issued, also 
regarding the enhancement of Moldova legislation in accordance 
with European standards, separation of state powers. The 
participation of Council of Europe observers in February 27th 
parliamentary elections was discusses, states a Parliament Press 
Service communique. 

</TEXT>

