<F P=100> CENTRAL ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Kazakhstan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Nazarbayev Issues Decree Creating State Treasury </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0302113294 Almaty Kazakh Radio Network in Russian 0700 GMT 
3 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0302113294 </F>
<F P=104>  Almaty Kazakh Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] President Nursultan Nazarbayev has issued a decree 
on setting up a Finance Ministry Treasury with the aim of 
effective control over revenues and expenditures in 
administering budget, raising the efficiency of financing state 
programs, and strengthening control over the proceeds, targeted 
and other kinds of use of state funds. It will consist of the 
main board, the ministry and its regional territorial missions, 
the towns Almaty and Leninsk, and districts in the cities and 
towns. 
  The treasury houses are charged with the task of supervising 
cash performance and republican budget's cash controlling, 
accounting of cash movement, servicing of external and internal 
debt of the republic, and regulating financial relations between 
the republican budget and the state non-budgetary funds. 
  The National Bank was authorized to supervise the cash 
performance of the republican budget in accordance with the 
existing law until the treasury bodies are fully formed. The 
treasury houses have the right to examine papers at the 
ministries, departments, enterprises, and organizations related 
to crediting, transferring, and using of sums of the republican 
budget. They also have the right to recover money of 
enterprises, works, and organizations, which were allocated from 
the republican budget and not being used by them properly. They 
can also impose sanctions on banks or other financial and credit 
enterprises for tardy crediting of funds entering the republican 
budget revenue, or funds that are credited from it to the 
recipients accounts at the relevant banks or financial and 
credit enterprises. 
  The Cabinet of Ministers was charged with the task of 
issuing 
a statute on formation and activities of the treasury houses, as 
well as to submit a proposal to the Supreme Soviet on amending 
the existing legislature related to assigning the Treasury 
bodies of rights to cash execution of the republican budget and 
granting it with other rights that will be stipulated by the 
statute. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

