<F P=100> Tajikistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Presidium Endorses New Government Structure </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0302112694 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 1000 GMT 
3 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0302112694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Mayak Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Presidium of the Supreme Soviet of the Republic 
of Tajikistan has endorsed the new structure and composition of 
the country's Council of Ministers. Henceforth, the republic 
will have 23 ministries and three state committees. Four deputy 
heads of government have been deprived of their posts; however, 
most ministers have kept their portfolios. A Ministry of 
Security has been formed. It has been decided that the decree 
of the Presidium of the Tajik Supreme Soviet will be submitted 
to the next session of the national parliament. 

</TEXT>

