<H3> <TI>   Envoy on Support for Incorporation Into EU </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0202200294 Riga Radio Riga Network in Latvian 1800 GMT 2 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0202200294 </F>
<F P=104>  Riga Radio Riga Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Latvian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] It is Germany's duty to promote Latvia's 
incorporation into the European Union emphasized the new German 
Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary Reinhard Holubek, 
meeting today with Prime Minister Valdis Birkavs. The envoy 
noted that Latvia's integration into Europe is currently delayed 
by the Russian troops. Therefore, Germany supports Latvia's 
demand for the withdrawal of the troops. Holubek expressed the 
conviction that, thanks to international pressure, the Russian 
troops will be withdrawn from Latvia by 31 August this year. 
Another delaying factor in Latvia's integration into Europe, 
the envoy believes, is the problem of the Skrunda radar station. 

</TEXT>

