<H3> <TI>   Premier Unsatisfied With Pace of Reform </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS0302101094 Vilnius ELTA in English 2208 GMT 2 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS0302101094 </F>
<F P=104>  Vilnius ELTA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From "News Bulletin" No. 428] </F>
  [Text] Vilnius, Feb 2, ELTA -- Speed of the agricultural 
reform is not satisfying neither to the government nor 
landowners, Prime Minister Adolfas Slezevicius told the national 
radio on Wednesday. 
  But he added that land was being returned quicker at the 
moment. He said in 1991-1992, the documents returning the 
property were handed to 12.6 thousand former landowners and only 
in 1993 -- 25.2 thousand. 
  Slezevicius said the reform would be speeded up when local 
authorities hire enough officials working with the land issues. 

</TEXT>

