<H3> <TI>   Minister Asks UN, CSCE To Condemn Azerbaijan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0202210094 Yerevan Armenia's Radio First Program Network 
in Armenian 1800 GMT 2 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0202210094 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan Armenia's Radio First Program Network 
in Armenian 1800 GMT 2 Feb 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Armenian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Armenian foreign minister sent letters today to 
Ronaldo Mota Sardenberg, the president of the UN Security 
Council, and Jan Eliasson, the chairman of the CSCE Minsk Group. 
  In noting the repeated Azerbaijani rejection of the peace 
plans of Russia and the CSCE, the shelling of and attacks 
against the territories of Nagorno-Karabakh and Armenia, and the 
internationalization of the Karabakh conflict, the foreign 
minister asked the CSCE Minsk Group to condemn the political and 
military actions of Azerbaijan and the UN Security Council to 
consider and implement necessary measures to force UN members to 
submit to UN resolutions. 

