<F P=101> Armenia </F>
<H3> <TI>   President Supports UN `Olympics Cease-Fire' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0202192294 Yerevan Armenia's Radio First Program Network 
in Armenian 1800 GMT 2 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0202192294 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan Armenia's Radio First Program Network 
in Armenian 1800 GMT 2 Feb 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Armenian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Armenian Foreign Ministry Press and Public 
Relations Service has reported that President Levon 
Ter-Petrosyan has sent a reply message to Juan Antonio 
Samaranch, the president of the International Olympics Committee 
[IOC], expressing his and his people's determination to help 
achieve the Olympics cease-fire between 5 February and 6 March 
1994 as declared by the 25 October 1993 resolution of the 48th 
session of the UN General Assembly at the initiative of the IOC. 
  The message also notes that the Armenian Republic and 
Nagorno-Karabakh accepted the UN Security Council resolutions on 
the peaceful resolution to the Karabakh problem and the peace 
plan of the CSCE Minsk Group, and has given a positive reply to 
all the proposals of the international community, particularly 
that of Russia, including Russia's latest proposal to establish 
a cease-fire as of 1 February 1994. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

