<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Officials, Groups Preview Yeltsin Visit </TI></H3>
<H4>   Official `Expects Much' From Talks </H4>
<F P=102> LD0202133894 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1217 GMT 2 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0202133894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Tengiz Pachkoria] </F>
  [Text] Tbilisi February 2 TASS -- Deputy Speaker of the 
Georgian Parliament Vakhtang Rcheulishvili said that Georgia 
"expects much from Boris Yeltsin's visit". "We hope that the 
Russian president's visit will set the beginning to the new 
stage in relations between the two countries", he said in an 
interview with the newspaper "SVOBODNAYA GRUZIA", published on 
Wednesday. 
  "The period of confrontation, covert and overt, is over", he 
said. "Economic, cultural and other ties must be restored. We 
expect that specific steps will be taken to ensure Georgia's 
territorial integrity and state interests". 

</TEXT>

