<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Grachev Arrives in Tbilisi; Visits Troops </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0202161094 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1450 
GMT 2 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0202161094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS special correspondents Albert Kochetkov and </F>
Mikhail Shevtsov] 
  [Text] Tbilisi, 2 Feb -- Immediately upon arrival at 
Vazyaniy Airport of the group of Russian troops in 
Transcaucasia, Russian Defense Minister Pavel Grachev paid a 
visit to the 405th motor rifle Regiment stationed here. 
Accompanied by commanders of the group of Russian troops in 
Transcaucasia, the head of the military department acquainted 
himself with the regiment's combat readiness, the 
professionalism of its personnel, and their morale. 
  During his meeting with commanders and officers of the unit 
and his tour of the military hardware fleet, of the canteen, and 
the barracks of the personnel, Grachev discussed the procurement 
of material and technical supplies, foodstuffs, and finances, as 
well as maintaining the present infrastructure, which includes 
military and civilian campuses, schools, and community 
facilities, in a good condition. 
  In an interview with an ITAR-TASS correspondent, the Russian 
defense minister expressed satisfaction with his visit to the 
regiment. "I came to Tbilisi on a working visit today to 
familiarize myself with the condition of the Russian military 
facilities located here, and to meet and talk with people, from 
the rank and file to the generals. But tomorrow I shall be 
taking part as a member of a Russian Government delegation in 
talks between Russian President Boris Yeltsin and Georgian Head 
of State Eduard Shevardnadze," the minister said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

