<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Soskovets, Kozyrev, Sobchak Accompany Yeltsin </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0302093294 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0856 
GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0302093294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS special correspondent Yuriy Sizov] </F>
  [Text] Tbilisi, 3 Feb -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin 
arrived in Tbilisi today. Among the Russian delegation 
accompanying the president were First Deputy Prime Minister Oleg 
Soskovets, Foreign Minister Andrey Kozyrev, and St. Petersburg 
Mayor Anatoliy Sobchak. Defense Minister Pavel Grachev arrived 
in Tbilisi yesterday. 
  The honored guest, the Russian head of state, was welcomed 
by 
the chairman of the Georgian parliament and head of state, 
Eduard Shevardnadze, Prime Minister Otar Patsatsia, members of 
the cabinet of ministers, the speaker and members of the 
Georgian parliament and officials of the head of state's staff. 
  The Russian president's official visit to Georgia has begun. 
A treaty on friendship, good-neighborliness and cooperation 
between the two states will be signed today. 

</TEXT>

