<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin, Shevardnadze Sign Treaty </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0302112994 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 1000 GMT 
3 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0302112994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Our correspondent reports that the presidents of 
Russia and Georgia have signed a treaty on friendship, 
goodneighborliness and cooperation between the two states. The 
treaty comprises 35 articles in which the contracting parties 
pledge to cooperate in the political, military and economic 
spheres. Experts are focusing most attention on those articles 
which acknowledge the inalienable rights of Russia and Georgia 
to adopt the necessary measures to protect their state borders. 
The sides will independently confront the questions of ensuring 
national security and defense construction, and in this regard 
will conduct close cooperation and practical interaction. 
  The sides will adopt measures to ensure the effective 
implementation of the agreement on the temporary sojourn of 
Russian troop formations on the territory of the Georgian 
Republic. 
  According to Article four, Russia and Georgia pledge not to 
take part in any alliances or blocs aimed against each other, 
nor will they render assistance to third states in the event of 
an outbreak of armed conflicts between these states and another 
party. 
  The current treaty covers a period of 10 years. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

