<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Explosion Kills Deputy Defense Minister </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0302092294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0918 GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0302092294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Albert Kochetkov] </F>
  [Text] Tbilisi February 3 TASS -- Georgian Deputy Defence 
Minister Nikolay Kekelidze was killed early on Thursday [3 
February] by an explosion in his own apartment in downtown 
Tbilisi, the Defence Ministry said and added that this was 
evidently an act of terrorism. 
  Kekelidze supervised the military-industrial complex and law 
enforcement agencies. 
  [Paris AFP in English at 0915 GMT on 3 Feb in a 
Moscow-datelined report adds: "The blast, which occurred around 
4:00 a.m. (0100 GMT), also killed another member of the 
minister's family."] 

</TEXT>

