<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Said To Disapprove of New Economists </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0202140094 Moscow Russian Television Network in Russian 
1100 GMT 2 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0202140094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Russian Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Vesti" newscast] </F>
  [Text] The Interfax agency reports, quoting a well-informed 
source close to Anatoliy Chubays: In the course of Chubays's 
recent telephone conversation with Boris Yeltsin, the president 
reacted negatively to the possibility of bringing in 
academicians [Leonid] Abalkin, [Nikolay] Petrakov, [Stanislav] 
Shatalin and others to work on adjusting reforms. According to 
Interfax's information, these economists have recently drawn up 
a report with a negative assessment of the course of economic 
reforms pursued for the past two years, and concluding that it 
was necessary to draw up a new socio-economic strategy. 

</TEXT>

