<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Gaydar Calls For Political Alliance </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0202143294 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 1200 GMT 
2 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0202143294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Yegor Gaydar, leader of the Russia's Choice bloc, 
has called on the Democratic Russia Movement to set up a 
political alliance. Such a party could coordinate actions to 
defend civil rights, counter communist and fascist propaganda, 
and conduct election campaigns more effectively. 
  Interfax has learned that Yegor Gaydar notes in a letter 
sent 
to the leadership of Democratic Russia that the December 
elections demonstrated what a broad base the conservatives and 
right-wing radicals have in our country. The present wavering 
government could kill the beginnings of stabilization and a new 
spiral of crisis could open the way to power for forces that 
would threaten Russia's very existence, Yegor Gaydar's message 
says. He also stresses that given the circumstances, all 
democratic forces needed to unite. 

</TEXT>

