<F P=100> Federal Assembly </F>
<H3> <TI>   Defense Committee Official Outlines Work Plans </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM0202155594 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA in Russian 2 Feb 94 
First Edition p 1 </F>

<F P=103> PM0202155594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Committee in Action"] </F>
  [Text] The Federation Council Committee for Security and 
Defense Questions has begun work. Yesterday there was a meeting 
with representatives of the Defense Ministry, and a special 
group was formed for dealings with the Federation Council 
Committee. Your ITAR-TASS correspondent was told this by Petr 
Shirshov, chairman of the Committee for Security and Defense 
Questions. 
  In its work the committee intends to "cooperate with the 
corresponding committees of the State Duma and also to expand 
contacts with the corresponding committees of the CIS 
countries." Petr Premyak, deputy chairman of the Committee for 
Security and Defense Questions, believes that the committee 
especially needs to cooperate with the corresponding committees 
in the Ukrainian parliament and in the parliaments of the Baltic 
states. 
  In Petr Shirshov's opinion, the committee will be guided in 
its activity by the Russian Federation Constitution, will also 
monitor the execution of the laws, and where necessary will 
prepare proposals and submit them in the form of legislative 
initiatives. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

